The following are major news items in leading Nigerian
Newspapers on Saturday. The Guardian: -- Nigeria is to host the cocoa
development meeting, which is made up of members of the west Africa
Committee of the Sustainable Tree Crops Program, next Monday and
Tuesday in Ibadan, southwest city of the west African country. This
Day: -- Nigerian Bureau of Public Enterprises has said it would sell
about 13 public enterprises, including National Electric Power
Authorities, Nigeria Telecommunication and the oil refineries, in the
second phase of the privatization program. The Post Express: -- More
than eight members of the entourage of Nigerian President Olusegun
Obasanjo were seriously injured Friday when six of the vehicles in
Obasanjo's convoy crashed into one another on the first day of the
president's visit to Bayelsa State, south of the country.
